Investor RelationsNASDAQ: SALMStock Info    Minimum 20 minute delay.Refresh DataAmerica's leading multimedia company specializing in Christian and conservative content 



      Corporate Profile          

Salem Media Group is America’s leading multimedia company specializing in Christian and conservative content, with media properties comprising radio, digital media and book, magazine and newsletter publishing. Each day Salem serves a loyal and dedicated audience of listeners and readers numbering in the millions nationally. With its unique programming focus, Salem provides compelling content, fresh commentary and relevant information from some of the most respected figures across the media landscape. Read More... 



      Featured Press Releases          



 




Salem Media Group Schedules Third Quarter 2016 Earnings Release and Teleconference
October 11, 2016
      Salem Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SALM) announced today that it plans to 
      report its third quarter 2016 financial results at 2:00 p.m. on November 
      7, 2016.
    
    
      The company also plans to host a teleconference to discuss its results 
      on November 7, 2016 at 2:00 p.m. Pacific...


Russ Whitnah Announces Planned Retirement
September 27, 2016
      Salem Media Group (NASDAQ: SALM), announced that after 23 years at the 
      helm in Philadelphia, Russ Whitnah has plans to retire as VP/GM at the 
      end of the year. Whitnah has been the "face" of Salem in Philly since 
      Salem's entry into the market. Salem purchased WFIL-AM in late 1993...


John Peroyea Resigns from Salem Media Group
September 12, 2016
      Salem 
      Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ: SALM), today announced that John 
      Peroyea has resigned from his role as VP Operations/VP/GM of 
      the Dallas cluster for Salem. This includes radio stations KLTY-FM, 
      KWRD-FM, KSKY-AM, KTNO-AM and KEXB-AM. John will serve as a Consultant...


 
 

