				July 17, 2017		



Salem Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SALM) acquire TradersCrux, to expand audience for marketing products and increasing advertising revenue





Salem Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SALM) announced that it has acquired TradersCrux. Roger Michalski, vice president and publisher of Eagle, said, “TradersCrux is a highly complementary acquisition for Eagle. With Eagle’s broad range of investing content and advice, we will be able to provide TradersCrux’s website visitors and newsletter subscribers an enhanced choice of investing resources. At the same time, adding TradersCrux gives Eagle an expanded audience for marketing its products and for increasing its advertising revenue.”
Salem Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SALM)’s stock on Friday traded at beginning with a price of $7.00 and when day-trade ended the stock finally surged 1.42% to reach at $7.15. Analyst’s mean target price for SALM is $9.00 while analysts mean recommendation is 1.50. Stock value has moved between $5 – 8.22 in last one year.
Analyst’s ratings play a very important role in outlining a stock’s performance. Let us check out how analysts have ranked SALM based on current scenarios. Stock has got OUTPERFORM rating from 1 analyst(s) whereas last month 1 analyst(s) have given outperform rating. SELL rating has been given by 0 analyst(s) and 1 analyst(s) given BUY rating to the stock. Company fiscal year is ending in December and analysts’ consensus recommendation is Buy for SALM and estimated EPS for next quarter is $ 0.15 .
Salem Media Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SALM) yearly performance is -9.72% and net profit margin is 3.50%. Annual EPS Growth of past 5 years is 5.80%. The current share price indicates that stock is -13.33% away from its one year high and is moving 43.00% ahead of its 52-week low.







On 14 July 2017, Westlake Chemical Corporation (NYSE:WLK) stock price started the day at $70.11 and moved between $69.69 – 70.59 to finally close at $70.24. WLK’s distance from 20 day simple moving average is 7.61% and distance from 50-Day simple moving average is 10.37%. In last 4 months performance of WLK was 12.01% while its price to sale ratio is 1.50 and price to book ratio is 2.48.
Analysts expect Westlake Chemical Corporation (NYSE:WLK) to report $ 1.21 EPS and has got OUTPERFORM rating from 7 of Thomson Reuters analysts and 0 analyst(s) given UNDERPERFORM rating. Analyst’s mean target price for WLK is $71.43 while analysts mean recommendation is 2.30. Firm LT growth rate is estimated as 8.00 %.
Cidara Therapeutics, Inc. (NASDAQ:CDTX)‘s stock on Friday traded at beginning with a price of $7.30 and when day-trade ended the stock finally surged 6.21% to reach at $7.70. Analyst’s mean target price for CDTX is $13.39 while analysts mean recommendation is 1.60. Stock value has moved between $5.66 – 13.05 in last one year.
Stock has got OUTPERFORM rating from 3 analyst(s) whereas last month 3 analyst(s) have given outperform rating. SELL rating has been given by 0 analyst(s) and 5 analyst(s) given BUY rating to the stock. Company fiscal year is ending in December and analysts’ consensus recommendation is Outperform for CDTX and estimated EPS for next quarter is $ -0.91 .
Cidara Therapeutics, Inc. (NASDAQ:CDTX) yearly performance is -28.44%. The current share price indicates that stock is -40.54% away from its one year high and is moving 36.28% ahead of its 52-week low.

 






 

